				<h2>Subjective questions - sometimes ok?</h2>
<p>Since I'm sure this'll come up sooner rather than later, should we allow <em>certain</em> subjective questions on Apple.SE? <a href="https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/82/applications-you-cant-live-without">This one</a> was just closed as subjective.</p>

<p>Subjective questions are frowned upon in SE sites and I have no argument that this particular question is quite subjective. But perhaps we prevent many more users from asking the same subjective question in the future by allowing a this one? Not necessarily my opinion, but there might be arguments that certain subjective questions are allowed, while most aren't.</p>

