				<h2>Answer</h2>
				<h3>Score ::2</h3>
				<p><p>Subjective questions for better or worse help out the community as it gets started - often as a way for users to boost rep to start getting several users to the point where editing and what normally takes a higher reputation to use. However I find their usefulness extremely short lived - they often become too vague or too localized and of little use even a week later. (Out of date and another answer among 9 million others isn't necessarily going to help).</p>

<p>A good example of a thread that could have been subjective but has become quite useful: <a href="https://superuser.com/questions/52483/terminal-tips-and-tricks-for-mac-os-x">Mac OS X Terminal Tips and Tricks</a> from Super User.</p>
</p><br>
